results.1-1: 一具插满细箭的肿胀的半身人尸体被挂在一根藤蔓上。（这个半身人侵犯了格龙蛙人的圣地，尸体被吊在这里示警。）
results.2-2: 一具未着护甲的类人生物骸骨被藤蔓绑在树上。（这名探险者被巴提利地精俘虏，涂满蜂蜜，任由饥饿的昆虫蚕食。）
results.3-3: 一具被碾碎的矮人遗骸，未着护甲，残留的痕迹表明她是被狂暴的恐龙踩死的。
results.4-4: 一具类人生物的遗骸，被啃食和烤焦了。（这个不幸的家伙被他的那些感染蓝雾热的饥饿同伴们谋杀并吃掉了。）
results.5-5: 一具血肉模糊的半精灵尸体，似乎被钝击致死。（她是被翼手兽从高空扔下来的。）
results.6-6: 一个矮人的四散骸骨，在被吃掉之前，先被撕成了碎片。（一群伶盗龙猎杀了这个矮人。）
results.7-7: 一具肿胀而发紫的精灵尸体，数天前刚被毒蛇咬死。
results.8-8: 一具新鲜的人类尸体，被塞到了一个树洞里。（四臂猩猩打算回来后再吃掉它。）
results.9-9: 一具类人生物骸骨，坐在营地折凳上，骷髅般的手里握着刀叉。
results.10-10: 一具侏儒尸体，干枯得只剩外皮，被巨蜘蛛的网缠成了茧状。
results.11-11: 一具人类尸体——只剩下腰部以上的部分了。迹象表明，这名探险者被暴龙咬成两半后，还爬了很远的距离。（在尸体上能发现一张“焰拳探险许可证”，其上信息表明此人是戴尔斯家族的奥诺万四世勋爵。）
results.12-12: 一条烧焦的蟒蛇骸骨，里面包着一具烧焦的精灵骸骨。（二者都死于@UUID[Compendium.dnd5e.spells.Item.IyikgTEOTv701jgQ]{闪电束}。）
results.13-13: 一具腐烂的巨蛙尸体，一柄短剑从它的背上刺出来。（把巨蛙剖开就会发现其体内有一具消化了一部分的半身人尸体。）
results.14-14: 一个斑猫人摊开四肢躺在地上，但四肢和头被从躯干上切了下来，并以错误的顺序粗糙地缝了回去。
results.15-15: 一名半兽人被一支三角龙的断角钉在了大树上。
results.16-16: 一具侏儒尸体被放在一个烧尽的火坑上，完全熟透但未被啃食。（地精武器和工具散落一旁，周围满是伶盗龙的足迹。）
results.17-17: 一具无头类人生物尸体倒挂在树上，六根巴提利地精之矛对称地刺穿了身体。（从袍子来看是红袍巫师，但头不见了。）
results.18-18: 一具精灵尸体平衡地挂在了离地 40 尺的树枝上，胳膊和腿垂了下来。（尸体和树枝间夹着一张纸条，说明精灵为了躲避四处觅食的异龙而爬上了树。他太害怕了，不敢下来。）
results.19-19: 一具正在腐烂的人类尸体，戴着焰拳头盔，双腿俱折。（他受到妖精龙的欢愉吐息影响，跳下了悬崖。一名同伴试图把他带回贝路利安堡，但他死在了途中。）
results.20-20: 一具矮人尸体，六个大洞刺进了她的护甲和胸部。（一头剑龙正好用尾击命中了她。）

results.1-1: 一只鹦鹉将粪便拉在随机一名角色头上。
results.2-2: 在港口附近，有一头正将船拖入仓库运货渠的@UUID[Actor.toaAnkylosaurus0]{甲龙}突然横冲直撞起来，它必须被安抚、控制或者杀死。
results.3-3: 一个商人喊到：“站住！小偷！”，同时一个@UUID[Actor.H6ajGPL3X6lzsQlc]{年轻人}冲过角色身旁。若小偷被抓，感激的商人会将角色们介绍给贸易亲王或另外帮他们一个忙。
results.4-4: 一个喝醉的外国水手（无护甲的@UUID[Actor.MIbGBptGOW5OSlHY]{老兵}）正大吵大闹，试图与三名当地@UUID[Actor.H6ajGPL3X6lzsQlc]{平民}打架，他们显然不是水手的对手。如果角色们介入争端，感激的当地人会成为可靠的南扎路港情报提供者，但那个水手与他的船员们将会在之后埋伏于城市的某处，袭击角色们。
results.5-5: 一个@UUID[Actor.H6ajGPL3X6lzsQlc]{乞丐}抓住一位角色的手并高喊：“那上古之人在禁城唤醒了一个可怕的新神！那些蛇人们知道！它们知道！”然后他磕磕绊绊地离开人群。路人告诉冒险者们不要理会这乞丐，而且他的预言大部分都是错的。
results.6-6: 警钟大响，宣告一群亡灵正攻击玛拉之喉。雇佣兵将怪物拦在城市中心外，但一些人被困在泰摩拉神殿并被一队怪物包围，这些怪物包括[[/r 2d6]]只@UUID[Actor.J6yWqkj0lotaRnTh]{丧尸}和[[/r 2d6]]具@UUID[Actor.pA11aGfCpX7OhuDH]{骷髅}，由 1 只@UUID[Actor.bSM1EJptwzV1JhjA]{食尸鬼}领导。如果角色们击败了这些亡灵，神殿会奖励他们 5 加仑的@UUID[Compendium.dnd-tomb-annihilation.items.Item.toaTejMugFortBel]{茶水}以及一瓶@UUID[Compendium.dnd5e.items.Item.ytlsBjYsZ7OBSEBs]{治疗药水}。
results.7-7: “小心！”的喊声给角色一个短暂的警告，紧接着一个水桶、建筑石块或其它重物砸了下来。角色必须通过一次 [[/save dex 12 format=long]]{DC 12 的敏捷豁免}，否则会被砸中，受到 [[/damage 4d6 bludgeoning average]]{14 (4d6) 点钝击伤害}。任何在通过一次[[/check perception 15 format=long]]{DC 15 的感知（察觉）检定}的角色会发现一个伪装的@UUID[Actor.toaYuantiPureblo]{纯血蛇人}正悄悄溜走。
results.8-8: 一个@UUID[Actor.s4zO6VOQ4fxzDNyB]{斑猫人诗人}（见@UUID[JournalEntry.toaAppDMonstersA.JournalEntryPage.FDyn4HWR2JU4EFY6]{附录 D}）向其中一名角色要一个金币来赌博，并承诺会还给该角色。如果角色同意，斑猫人会在第二天兑现承诺，归还一个装有[[/award 10gp]]{10 gp}的钱袋。
results.9-9: 一个@UUID[Compendium.dnd5e.monsters.Actor.13K3XK2A3wwxVKLD]{小偷}正试图偷窃一名角色的包裹。

results.1-1: 我的导师给过我一本写满知识和智慧的日志。它的丢失将使我崩溃。
results.2-2: 我曾与原始部落或宗族的人们共同生活过，现在我渴望回去看看他们过的怎么样。
results.3-3: 多年前，悲剧袭击了我所结交的一个孤立社会的成员，我将向他们致敬。
results.4-4: 我想学习更多让我着迷的类人文化。
results.5-5: 我向一个已经被抹去的宗族、部落、王国或是帝国寻求复仇。
results.6-6: 我有一件饰品，并且相信它是寻找一个失落已久的社会的关键。

results.1-1: 从我孩提时代起，我就听说过失落之城的故事。我下定决心要找到它，了解它藏有的秘密，并在史书里留下我的位置。
results.2-2: 我想找到我的导师，他在之前的一次探险中消失了。
results.3-3: 我有一个好对手。我俩之中只有一个是最棒的，而我会证明那个人是我。
results.4-4: 我不会出售任何具有历史意义或已成孤品的艺术品或其他宝物。
results.5-5: 我暗恋着赞助我进行考古发掘的人。
results.6-6: 我希望为一座图书馆、博物馆或大学带来声望。

results.71-75: 1 @UUID[Actor.toaYuantiAbomina]{yuan-ti abomination} arriving at the temple to challenge @UUID[Actor.zwk4UdGbwhWumFqp]{Ras Nsi’s} leadership. If @UUID[Actor.toaFenthaza00000]{Fenthaza} is alive, she uses her influence to arrange a showdown between Ras Nsi and the abomination in the fane (@UUID[JournalEntry.toaCh4Locationsi.JournalEntryPage.jDapyFVU0c9UoIBn]{area 9}). If Fenthaza is incapacitated or dead, the abomination bullies its way to Ras Nsi’s throne room (@UUID[JournalEntry.toaCh4Locationsi.JournalEntryPage.levHlyIkCVBQVoEj]{area 11}), where it is killed.
results.76-85: [[/r 2d4]] @UUID[Compendium.dnd5e.monsters.Actor.tYfQIxCJT0WaaKmc]{cult fanatics} (NE male and female humans of mixed ethnicities) seeking an audience with Ras Nsi, to pledge their devotion to Dendar the Night Serpent. The cult fanatics bring tribute in the form of treasure (roll once on the Treasure Hoard: Challenge 0–4 table in chapter 7 of the Dungeon Master’s Guide).
results.86-100: [[/r 2d6]] @UUID[Actor.ogAVSIzos9mQ3kqC]{tribal warriors} (N male and female Chultan humans) delivering tribute to Ras Nsi. This tribute consists of food, drink, and treasure (roll once on the Treasure Hoard: Challenge 0–4 table in chapter 7 of the Dungeon Master’s Guide).

results.1-5: The armillary sphere and any creatures inside it disappear. The DM ultimately decides where they end up, if anywhere. Possibilities include Mechanus, the Vast Swamp on Oerth, Mount Nevermind on Krynn, a desert on Athas, Victorian London on Earth, or the sun.
results.6-15: The creature sitting in the armillary chair is touched by an unknown entity and suffers a radical personality change. Work with the player to determine an appropriate change.
results.16-30: A @UUID[Compendium.dnd5e.spells.Item.LkvI11Uue774QBKZ]{cloudkill} spell is cast within the globe.
results.31-50: The sun-shaped orb splits open, spilling [[/award 5000gp]] onto the floor.
results.51-65: The creature sitting in the armillary chair gains a charm of heroism (see “Supernatural Gifts” in chapter 7 of the Dungeon Master’s Guide).
results.66-80: Every creature within 20 feet of the armillary sphere regains [[/heal 50]]{50 hit points}. Creatures inside the globe do not gain this benefit.
results.81-90: A @UUID[Compendium.dnd5e.items.Item.thkvJ5QBRORIwkkV]{gem of brightness} appears on the lap of the creature seated in the armillary chair.
results.91-99: The Intelligence score of the creature seated in the armillary chair permanently increases by [[/r 1d4 + 1]], up to a maximum of 22.
results.100-100: The creature seated in the armillary chair is granted the ability to cast the @UUID[Compendium.dnd5e.spells.Item.3okM6Gn63zzEULkz]{wish} spell once.

results.1-6: The demon faces exhale jets of a soporific gas that dissipates quickly. Each creature in the room that is not immune to the poisoned condition must succeed on a [[/save con 15 format=long]] or fall &Reference[unconscious apply=false]{unconscious}. An unconscious creature can repeat the saving throw each time it takes damage, ending the effect on itself on a success.
results.7-12: The demon faces exhale jets of sparkling dust, which blind any creature in the room that does not succeed on a [[/save wis 15 format=long]]. A creature’s blindness lasts until it is cured with a @UUID[Compendium.dnd5e.spells.Item.F0GsG0SJzsIOacwV]{lesser restoration} spell or similar magic.
results.13-18: Stone spikes 6 inches long magically protrude from the walls. Any creature that takes damage from the room at the start of its turn takes an additional [[/damage 2d10 piercing average]] damage from the spikes. The spikes retract when the next room effect is triggered.
results.19-20: The demon faces spew jets of an incendiary gas that promptly ignites, filling the room with fire. Each creature in the room takes [[/damage 10d8 fire average]] damage.

results.1-5: Bird folk inhabit a monastery that hangs on the side of a plateau many miles up the Olung River, past the Laughing Gorge. The bird folk are holding the last royal heir of Chult as their prisoner.
results.6-12: Deep in the heart of the jungle is a city built by minotaurs. It’s now overrun by snake people, but even worse things dwell below. In visions, I have seen strange devils screaming in the dark.
results.13-17: If you head up the Tiryki River about five days by canoe, you’ll see a stone spire to the east. Natives call it Firefinger. “Terror folk” nest there, and if they spot you, you’re in for a fight.
results.18-22: One must purchase a charter of exploration at Fort Beluarian before undertaking any jungle expedition. The Flaming Fist punishes explorers who don’t have the required paperwork.
results.23-28: Chult had many kings and queens, but none more beautiful than Queen Zalkoré. Thousands of warriors killed and died for her, but the only memorial of her reign is the garden palace of Nangalore, which lies near the eastern shore of the River Olung, north of Lake Luo.
results.29-33: Chult was once a playground for a green dragon. Her bones mark the location of a hidden treasure trove. If you travel to Mezro and head east across the Laughing Gorge, then south toward Kir Sabal, you might stumble on the dragon’s bones and earn yourself a place in the history books!
results.34-40: The city of Mezro was not destroyed during the Spellplague after all. Its ruins are an illusion. I heard a pale-skinned man whisper this to a dinosaur man with a big sword. The dinosaur man smelled like honeysuckle.
results.41-45: Dwarves are determined to reclaim Wyrmheart Mine, but a red dragon lives there now. Haven’t seen one of them in a while.
results.46-50: The jungle is full of nature spirits — weird little elemental creatures with masks. They don’t speak, and I’ve never known one to be harmful, but their magical powers should not be taken lightly.
results.51-55: Some city folk were expecting the arrival of a Halruaan airship called the Star Goddess. It never arrived. I bet it crashed in the jungle somewhere.
results.56-60: There are giant snapping turtles in Snapping Turtle Bay. One of them is as big as a house. He’s known as King Toba, and his shell has gemstones embedded in it.
results.61-65: The Order of the Gauntlet came here to cleanse the jungle of undead. They lost one of their encampments not too long ago. They’re just barely hanging on to another one. I see their emissaries all the time, heading up the River Soshenstar in canoes to get more supplies and templars from Port Nyanzaru.
results.66-71: Watch out for any mist with a blue tinge to it. It spreads a fever that causes magical hallucinations.
results.72-77: 一只名为阿雷玛格的龙龟栖息在楚尔特海湾。如果你想从南扎路港起航，你需要财宝才能安抚这只贪婪的怪物。具体要多少财宝，我说不准。阿雷玛格会告诉你它想要什么，最好照它说的做。
results.78-82: A ruined city lies up the River Tath, past Kahakla Gorge. Supposedly, no one’s explored past the gorge, but that’s not true. It’s just that the few who made it out alive mostly keep quiet about what they found there. I have it on good authority that the ruins are guarded by a naga who is both wise and generous.
results.83-87: The great god Ubtao once guided the people of Chult, be he tired of their constant warring and abandoned them. Since then, Chultans have turned to the worship of other gods, some of which were tricksters and deceivers.
results.88-92: Long ago, a peaceful tribe of fisherfolk called the Aldani angered Ubtao by catching and eating all the lobsters in a river. As punishment for their greed, they were all transformed into monsters that dwell in the Aldani Basin.
results.93-96: Perched atop a plateau overlooking the Aldani Basin is a ghost village. All the people there disappeared. No one knows why. You can reach the Aldani Basin by following the River Soshenstar.
results.97-100: The great god Ubtao loved mazes. If you happen upon a maze of any kind, trace a path through it. You will earn Ubtao’s favor by doing so.

results.1-1: Boats make me seasick.
results.2-2: I talk to myself, and I don’t make friends easily.
results.3-3: I believe that I’m intellectually superior to people from other cultures and have much to teach them.
results.4-4: I’ve picked up some unpleasant habits living among goblins, lizardfolk, or orcs.
results.6-6: I wear a tribal mask and never take it off.

results.1-1: I have a secret fear of some common wild animal — and in my work, I see them everywhere.
results.2-2: I can’t leave a room without searching it for secret doors.
results.3-3: When I’m not exploring dungeons or ruins, I get jittery and impatient.
results.4-4: I have no time for friends or family. I spend every waking moment thinking about and preparing for my next expedition.
results.5-5: When given the choice of going left or right, I always go left.
results.6-6: I can’t sleep except in total darkness.

results.1-1: Discovery. I want to be the first person to discover a lost culture. (Any)
results.2-2: Distance. One must not interfere with the affairs of another culture — even one in need of aid. (Lawful)
results.3-3: Knowledge. By understanding other races and cultures, we learn to understand ourselves. (Any)
results.4-4: Power. Common people crave strong leadership, and I do my utmost to provide it. (Lawful)
results.5-5: Protection. I must do everything possible to save a society facing extinction. (Good)
results.6-6: Indifferent. Life is cruel. What’s the point in saving people if they’re going to die anyway? (Chaotic)

results.1-1: Preservation. That artifact belongs in a museum. (Good)
results.2-2: Greed. I won’t risk my life for nothing. I expect some kind of payment. (Any)
results.3-3: Death Wish. Nothing is more exhilarating than a narrow escape from the jaws of death. (Chaotic)
results.4-4: Dignity. The dead and their belongings deserve to be treated with respect. (Lawful)
results.5-5: Immortality. All my exploring is part of a plan to find the secret of everlasting life. (Any)
results.6-6: Danger. With every great discovery comes grave danger. The two walk hand in hand. (Any)

results.1-1: The creature drinking the water must make a [[/save con 12 format=long]], taking [[/damage 8d10 necrotic average]] damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. If this damage reduces the creature to 0 hit points, it dies and turns to dust.
results.2-2: The creature drinking the water loses the ability to speak for 8 hours. A @UUID[Compendium.dnd5e.spells.Item.F0GsG0SJzsIOacwV]{lesser restoration} spell or similar magic ends this effect.
results.3-3: The creature drinking the water magically changes sex. A @UUID[Compendium.dnd5e.spells.Item.WzvJ7G3cqvIubsLk]{greater restoration} spell restores the creature’s original sex, as does another drink from the fountain that yields this same result.
results.4-4: The creature drinking the water gains [[/heal 2d10 temp]].

results.1-1: I prefer the company of those who aren’t like me, including people of other races.
results.2-2: I’m a stickler when it comes to observing proper etiquette and local customs.
results.3-3: I would rather observe than meddle.
results.4-4: By living among violent people, I have become desensitized to violence.
results.5-5: I would risk life and limb to discover a new culture or unravel the secrets of a dead one.
results.6-6: When I arrive at a new settlement for the first time, I must learn all its customs.

results.1-1: [[/r 2d6]] @UUID[Compendium.dnd-tomb-annihilation.items.Item.toafafDancingMon]{dancing monkey fruit} growing on a tree
results.2-2: Menga bush with [[/r 2d6]] @UUID[Compendium.dnd-tomb-annihilation.items.Item.toafafMengaLeave]{ounces of leaves}

results.1-1: Treasure lies at the foot of the statue, left there as tribute by some jungle creature. Roll once on the @UUID[Compendium.dnd-tomb-annihilation.tables.RollTable.dmgTreasureDrops]{Treasure Drops} table to determine what treasure is found. If the roll indicates no treasure, the characters find worthless pieces of bone jewelry instead.
results.2-2: Goblin, grung, and su-monster skulls are piled around the statue’s base.
results.3-3: A @UUID[Compendium.dnd5e.spells.Item.pB7XVYwdGNcUG935]{glyph of warding} is inscribed on the statue. To spot the glyph, a character searching the statue must succeed on a [[/check investigation 15 format=long]]. If any creature touches the statue, the glyph erupts with magical energy in a 20-foot-radius sphere centered on the statue. Each creature in the area must succeed on a [[/save dex 14 format=long]], taking [[/damage 5d8 thunder average]] damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. The thunderous noise has a [[/r 1d100cs<=75#Sturges or a troll hears the noise on a result of 1]]{75 percent chance} of attracting stirges or a troll lurking nearby (see “@UUID[JournalEntry.toaAppBRandomEnc.JournalEntryPage.mJLP1CT91yz4xyEu]{Stirges}” and “@UUID[JournalEntry.toaAppBRandomEnc.JournalEntryPage.gqmqw9126FVmMnBl]{Troll}”).
results.4-4: The statue has grooves carved into its stomach that form a maze. Any character who studies the grooves and succeeds on a [[/check int 10 format=long]] sees a clear pathway through the labyrinth. That character is then bestowed with the power to cast the @UUID[Compendium.dnd5e.spells.Item.cYI4RNNjI5GAmLhy]{find the path} spell as an action, no components required, by tracing the same path with his or her finger. Once used, this ability goes away. Once the statue has granted this benefit, it can’t do so again until the next dawn.

results.13-13: @UUID[Actor.toaCh2AssassinVi]{1d3 assassin vines} (see @UUID[JournalEntry.toaAppDMonstersA]{appendix D}) blending in with the surrounding walls.
results.16-16: The characters hear a throaty croak that sounds at once both lusty and forlorn. Its source cannot be ascertained.
results.18-19: A concealed pit 5 feet wide, 10 feet deep, and lined with poisoned wooden stakes. The lead character spots the pit with a successful [[/check perception 15 format=long]]. The first character to step on a pit falls in, taking [[/damage 1d6 bludgeoning average]] damage and landing on [[/r 1d4]] stakes, each of which deals [[/damage 1d6 piercing & 2d6 poison average]] damage.
results.20-20: An interior secret door. It requires a successful [[/check perception 15 format=long]] to spot.

results.1-1: I love a good puzzle or mystery.
results.2-2: I’m a pack rat who never throws anything away.
results.3-3: Fame is more important to me than money.
results.4-4: I have no qualms about stealing from the dead.
results.5-5: I’m happier in a dusty old tomb than I am in the centers of civilization.
results.6-6: Traps don’t make me nervous. Idiots who trigger traps make me nervous.
results.7-7: I might fail, but I will never give up.
results.8-8: You might think I’m a scholar, but I love a good brawl. These fists were made for punching.

results.43-44: Chult is strewn with the corpses and bones of those who have fallen victim to its terrors. When the characters discover one such victim, roll a [[/r d20]] and consult the @UUID[Compendium.dnd-tomb-annihilation.tables.RollTable.dmgRanEncDeadExp]{Dead Explorers} table to determine what they find. Then roll once on the @UUID[Compendium.dnd-tomb-annihilation.tables.RollTable.dmgTreasureDrops]{Treasure Drops} table to see what, if anything, can be found on or near the remains.
